lso   Farley  ,   Fairley  ,   Fairlie  ."]},{"name":"Farlow","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Shropshire, so named from Old English <i>fearn</i> ‘fern’ + <i>hlāw</i> ‘hill, tumulus’. This surname may have become confused with   Farley  ."]},{"name":"Fearnley","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): from any of various places called with Old English <i>fearn</i> ‘fern, bracken’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, clearing’, notably the Yorkshire places Farnley near Otley, Farnley near Armley, Farnley Tyas, Fearnley in Wyke, Fernley Hill in Altofts, and perhaps also Fernilee in Derbyshire.","English: variant of   Farley  ."]},{"name":"Farlee","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Farley  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old French <i>Marie</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Moira","meanings":["Anglicized form of Irish Máire , now used throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705208,"age":0,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":13,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":33,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Farley was born in 1587, in Ware, Hertfordshire, England, her father, Richard Farley, was 33 and her mother, Elizabeth, was 33. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Robert Hutchins. She died in 1640, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1587–1640":"1587–1640","1584–1648":"1584–1648","1600–1665":"1600–1665","1611–1685":"1611–1685","1554–Male":"1554–Surnud","1554–Female":"1554–Surnud","1600":"1600","1611":"1611","1665":"1665","1587":"1587","1620":"1620","1554":"1554","1685":"1685","1640":"1640","1574":"1574","1584":"1584","1648":"1648","Towcester, Northamptonshire, England":"Towcester, Northamptonshire, England","Ware, Hertfordshire, England":"Ware, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1587–1640":"1587–1640","1584–1648":"1584–1648","1600–1665":"1600–1665","1611–1685":"1611–1685","1554–Male":"1554–Kuollut","1554–Female":"1554–Kuollut","1600":"1600","1611":"1611","1665":"1665","1587":"1587","1620":"1620","1554":"1554","1685":"1685","1640":"1640","1574":"1574","1584":"1584","1648":"1648","Towcester, Northamptonshire, England":"Towcester, Northamptonshire, England","Ware, Hertfordshire, England":"Ware, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1587–1640